- display stray whitespace
from claude:
Add this to your nvim config:
luavim.opt.list = true
vim.opt.listchars = { trail = '•' }
Replace • with whatever character you prefer, e.g. ·, ␣, or ~.

set listchars=tab:»·,trail:·

If you also want to highlight it more visibly:
luavim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'TrailingWhitespace', { bg = 'red' })
vim.fn.matchadd('TrailingWhitespace', [[\s\+$]])

Or with a simple autocmd to only highlight in normal mode (avoids annoyance while typing):
lualocal tw = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup('TrailingWhitespace', {})
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('InsertLeave', {
    group = tw,
    callback = function()
        vim.fn.matchadd('TrailingWhitespace', [[\s\+$]])
    end,
})
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('InsertEnter', {
    group = tw,
    callback = function()
        vim.fn.clearmatches()
    end,
})
The listchars approach is the simplest; the highlight approach is more visually obvious.
